				\begin{document}$$qg \rightarrow t \rightarrow W(\rightarrow \ell \nu )\,b$$\end{document} process. Events are characterised by an isolated high-energy charged lepton (electron or muon), missing transverse momentum from the neutrino and exactly one jet produced by the hadronisation of the b-quark. Events with a W boson decaying into a τ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
