				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$1.375 < |\eta | < 3.2$$\end{document}. An iron/scintillator tile calorimeter provides hadronic energy measurements in the central pseudorapidity range. The endcap and forward regions are instrumented with LAr calorimeters for both the electromagnetic and hadronic energy measurements, and extend the coverage to |η|=4.9\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
