For the single top-quark processes, variations of initial- and final-state radiation (ISR and FSR) together with variations of the hard-process scale are studied. The uncertainty is estimated using events generated with Powheg interfaced to Pythia. Factorisation and renormalisation scales are varied independently by factors of 0.5 and 2.0, while the scale of the parton shower is varied consistently with the renormalisation scale using specialised Perugia 2012 tunes [44]. The uncertainty on the amounts of ISR and FSR in the simulated tt¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
